    "(6)The frequency mask M ∈ {0, 1} H×W is defined by:M(u, v) = 1, if max(|u -H 2 |, |v -W 2 |) ≤ ρ H 2 0, otherwise(7)Thereafter, the LF and HF features are independently passed through two distinct low-rank linear projection layers, generating frequency adaptation adjustments:∆F low i = Adapter i 2 (F low i),(8)∆F high i = Adapter i 3 (F high i).",
    "(9) The Frequency Adapters shares the same structure as the Spatial Adapter, as defined in Equation 4.Dynamic Router.",
